      <h3>
  
    
      <a href="/blog/climate/uk-pact-quit-coal-huge-win-climate-20150219-0">Political pact to quit coal is a win for the climate</a>
      </h3>
  

      <div class="field_body">
  
    
      It's not often that politicians put aside their differences to work together. But last weekend, with little fanfare, David Cameron, Nick Clegg, and Ed Miliband signed up to a new pact – an agreement to work together to tackle climate change.
      </div>
  

      <div class="node_by">
  
    
      Posted by Richard Casson - 19 February, 2015 - 11:45 - <a href="http://www.greenpeace.org.uk/blog/climate/uk-pact-quit-coal-huge-win-climate-20150219-0#disqus_thread" class="comments disqus-comments" title="Jump to the comments of this posting.">Comments</a>
      </div>
  

