      </div>
  

      <h3>
  
    
      <a href="/blog/climate/great-news-uk-makes-pact-quit-climate-wrecking-coal-20150216">Great news! UK makes pact to quit climate-wrecking coal</a>
      </h3>
  

      <div class="field_body">
  
    
      In case you missed it, on Saturday we heard some big news. In a surprising move in the run up to the general election, David Cameron, Nick Clegg and Ed Miliband launched a joint pact stating that the UK will aim to the first major economy to end unabated coal burning.
      </div>
  

      <div class="node_by">
  
    
      Posted by Lawrence Carter - 16 February, 2015 - 10:48 - <a href="http://www.greenpeace.org.uk/blog/climate/great-news-uk-makes-pact-quit-climate-wrecking-coal-20150216#disqus_thread" class="comments disqus-comments" title="Jump to the comments of this posting.">Comments</a>
      </div>
  

